{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "615454d7f1c8d7ef02ee07dd", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": null, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": null, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "NTAS1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76e4c52ffa3c944600e1"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eba2"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [{"title": "NTA Abhyas Paper", "value": "107", "isVisible": true}], "previousYearPapers": [], "question": {"text": "A ray of light is incident on the plane mirror at rest. The mirror starts turning at a uniform angular acceleration of <math><mi>\u03c0</mi></math> rad <math><msup><mrow><mtext>s</mtext></mrow><mrow><mo>\u2013</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>. The reflected ray at the end of <math><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&nbsp;s</mi></math> must have turned through", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "IwUv2", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>90</mn><mo>&#xB0;</mo></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "DAxfw", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>45</mn><mo>&#xB0;</mo></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "gGzHn", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>22.5</mn><mo>&#xB0;</mo></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "hLGbl", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>11.25</mn><mo>&#xB0;</mo></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "As we know, if a mirror is rotated.<br /><br />Given, angular acceleration, <math><mi>\u03b1</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>\u03c0&nbsp;</mi><mrow><mrow><mtext>r</mtext><mtext>a</mtext><mtext>d</mtext></mrow><mo>/</mo><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>s</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mrow></math><br /><br />Initial angular velocity <math><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi>\u03c9</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math><br /><br />Time, <math><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac><mtext>&nbsp;s</mtext></math><br /><br />Now, as <math><mi>\u03b8</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi>\u03c9</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>\u03b1</mi><msup><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math><br /><br /><math><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>\u00d7</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>\u00d7</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi><mo>\u00d7</mo><msup><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math><br /><br /><math><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>180</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u00d7</mo><mn>16</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msup><mrow><mn>5.625</mn></mrow><mrow><mtext>o</mtext></mrow></msup></math><br /><br />Since, mirror is turned by <math><msup><mrow><mn>5.625</mn></mrow><mrow><mtext>o</mtext></mrow></msup></math>, therefore reflected ray will be turned by <math><mn>2</mn><mo>\u00d7</mo><mn>5.625</mn><mo>=</mo><msup><mrow><mn>11.25</mn></mrow><mrow><mtext>o</mtext></mrow></msup></math>.<br /><br />Hence, option <math><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mtext>4</mtext></mrow></mfenced></math> is correct.", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f4831